com.vernalis.pdbconnector.config

Class ReportField2

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vernalis.pdbconnector.config.ReportField2
  • Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public class ReportField2
extends java.lang.Object
    ReportField class. A ReportField represents a single report column, and defines:
    • UI label
    • String to use in report request
    • Report table column type
    • Report table column name (default is same as UI label)
    • Default status (selected or unselected)
    • Triggers (other report fields, report categories, or standard reports that will trigger the selection of this field)
    SDR 07/Jul/2016 - Added support for ListCells, indicated by presence of optional 'deliminator' attribute in XML
    See Also:
    ReportCategory2, StandardReport

      • isPrimaryCitationSuffix

        public final boolean isPrimaryCitationSuffix()
        Deprecated. 
        Checks if this is the hidden report field controlling the primary citation suffix. The primary citation suffix field is defined by the special name "PRIMARY_CITATION_SUFFIX". This hidden pseudo field is triggered automatically by selection of any field in the primary citation category, and should not be user-selectable in the UI. Unlike all other report fields, the primary citation suffix does not represent a column in the KNIME output table. Rather, it is a modifier of the behaviour of the citation report fields. Hence, the string value represented by this field should be appended to the custom report URL, and should not be concatenated with the regular report fields.
        Returns:
        true, if is primary citation suffix.
